1
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:47,720
Pan is a regular of mine.

2
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:49,690
He came to borrow money yesterday.

3
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,620
Considering our friendship,

4
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,840
I lent it to him.

5
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,729
Then what was his reason for borrowing money?

6
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,680
Do you know what he does for a living?

7
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,480
He once said he was a cloth merchant.

8
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:06,200
But he really didn't mention the reason for borrowing.

9
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,280
But these days,

10
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:09,919
who doesn't have difficulties living away from home?

11
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:11,720
If he doesn't say, I won't ask.

12
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,680
He's a grave robber.

13
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,440
He's a grave robber.

14
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,040
We found his body by the moat

15
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:24,760
at Hai hour last night.

16
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,680
Then he also stole my husband's remains.

17
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,040
According to his account before he died,

18
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,520
he indeed did it.

19
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,720
He found treasures in the tomb

20
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:36,120
and acquired a windfall because of it.

21
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,800
That's impossible.

22
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:40,560
I arranged my late husband's funeral myself.

23
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,440
There were no treasures in the coffin.

24
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,840
If he said so,

25
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,800
it must be a scam.

26
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,210
We also can't figure out

27
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:50,400
why he stole your husband's remains.

28
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,480
Then how did your husband die?

29
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,960
Died of alcoholism.

30
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:03,200
How was your relationship as a couple?

31
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,880
That's all in the past.

32
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,880
He was a merchant.

33
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,040
He cared for me deeply.

34
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:22,280
I thought I had found a good husband,

35
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,160
so I married him.

36
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,960
But after we got married,

37
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,880
he became an alcoholic and a gambler.

38
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:31,280
He wouldn't stop until he lost everything.

39
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,280
Over time,

40
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:37,320
the business also declined due to his absurd behavior.

41
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:42,040
And my emotional support was all placed on Acai.

42
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:46,960
It became the best companion in my life.

43
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,120
Do you like it?

44
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,440
Acai.

45
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,360
This is called a longevity tag.

46
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,120
Your name is engraved on it.

47
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:58,200
This way, you won't get lost anymore.

48
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,880
Let's go back.

49
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,320
People can't even get enough to eat,

50
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,560
and you're feeding milk to this beast.

51
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,880
Go make me a bowl of noodles.

52
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,680
What are you doing?

53
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,640
This must be worth a lot of money.

54
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,200
I'll pawn it.

55
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,800
I can definitely get my money back.

56
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,000
This belongs to Acai. Give it back to me.

57
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,880
Let go,

58
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,480
or I'll sell it too.

59
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,800
Acai.

60
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,880
I'm sorry.

61
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:54,880
This longevity pendant is not made of silver.

62
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,520
But he will never take it away again.

63
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,360
Where is the money?

64
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,840
Don't mention it.

65
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,720
I had bad luck today.

66
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:12,480
Played ten rounds. None of them came up big.

67
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:16,960
Go get me a basin of water to wash my feet and wash away the bad luck.

68
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:31,240
You always say you'll win it back.

69
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,280
But you end up losing everything.

70
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,560
You should really quit gambling.

71
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,880
I'll quit.

72
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,720
I'll look for a job tomorrow.

73
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,560
You say that every time.

74
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,040
I mean it this time.

75
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,080
Why does it smell like urine?

76
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,600
It might be Acai's pee.

77
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,120
I'll clean it up later.

78
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,920
Damn it. This dog has grown so big but still doesn't bark.

79
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,920
What's the point of keeping it?

80
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,520
I'm going to sell you today.

81
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,280
What are you doing?

82
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:17,080
If you dare touch Acai, I'll fight you to the death.

83
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,960
Fight me?

84
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,200
Ever since that dog came here,

85
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:22,200
my luck has been getting worse. I lose every bet.

86
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,040
I must sell it today no matter what.

87
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,040
Don't touch it.

88
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,720
Let go! Acai!

89
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,720
Wait, I have money.

90
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,160
I have money.

91
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,840
Wait, I have money.

92
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:35,400
I have money. Let Acai go.

93
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:36,640
Let it go.

94
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,840
I have money.

95
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,400
Wow, Xia Chunyi.

96
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,800
You really paid a high price for this dog.

97
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,440
Acai!

98
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,280
Acai!

99
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,560
Acai!

100
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,640
Acai!

101
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,680
Acai!

102
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,400
Where is Acai? Where did you take it?

103
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,080
Stop pulling me. I sold it.

104
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,240
Sold it?

105
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,280
Where did you sell it?

106
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:35,679
The ghost market.

107
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,440
You bastard!

108
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,200
Don't go.

109
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,480
The dealers wouldn't take it,

110
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,880
so I threw it in the ruins.

111
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:51,100
I regretted it later and went looking for it.

112
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,040
The vendor told me it was too cold,

113
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,770
and it froze to death in no time.

114
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,600
What's wrong?

115
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,080
I just drank too much.

116
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,800
I don't remember what I did.

117
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:17,080
Besides, didn't I go back to look for it?

118
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,680
Don't be mad, honey.

119
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,680
I promise I won't drink anymore.

120
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,120
I won't gamble either, okay?

121
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,320
I will work hard

122
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,000
and earn good money.

123
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,400
Don't be mad.

124
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,960
I'll start working right now, look.

125
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:50,080
Give me back Acai!

126
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,360
Give me back Acai! Are you done?

127
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,600
Give me back Acai!

128
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:59,300
Have you made enough of a scene? Do you still want to live together?

129
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,400
Acai!

130
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,560
When he treated you like that,

131
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,890
why didn't you report to the authorities?

132
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:11,560
What good would reporting it do for a woman like me?

133
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:14,160
They'd lock him up for a few days and let him out.

134
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,240
My life would only get harder.

135
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:20,090
Why don't you government officials do anything?

136
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,650
I was just born too late.

137
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:24,080
Otherwise, I would definitely arrest him.

138
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:29,120
Later, I searched for a whole day but couldn't find Acai.

139
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,600
Acai, where are you?

140
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:36,200
Excuse me, have you seen a little yellow dog about this big?

141
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,080
His name is Acai.

142
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,240
Never seen him.

143
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,200
Sir, have you seen a dog about this big?

144
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,720
Never seen him. Acai!

145
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,800
Go away. I haven't seen him. My dog is named Acai.

146
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,460
Go away. I haven't seen him. My dog is named Acai.

147
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,280
Maybe heaven was watching.

148
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,720
When I got home, I found that

149
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,240
he had suffered a sudden stroke from heavy drinking

150
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,040
and already passed away.

151
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:01,240
The neighbor called the officers and a doctor

152
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,960
to examine the body.

153
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:06,140
He was only buried after confirming he died of illness.

154
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,760
For the sake of our marriage,

155
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:10,440
I arranged his funeral.

156
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,640
But after all these years,

157
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,160
I've never visited his grave.

158
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,040
From the day he was buried,

159
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,760
our bond came to an end.

160
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:29,840
Sorry to bother you today.

161
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,080
If we find any other clues,

162
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,520
we will come back to ask.

163
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:36,600
I also didn't expect that Pan would meet with an accident.

164
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,560
I might be the last person he saw.

165
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,560
But I was at Yichun Pavilion all day yesterday.

166
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,880
You happened to be there too,

167
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,280
so you can testify for me.

168
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,360
Stop. Take two steps forward.

169
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,880
You missed your mark.

170
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,240
Before the guqin music starts,

171
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,560
you need to walk here in advance.

172
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:54,690
And light the candles at the same time.

173
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:55,840
Okay.

174
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,200
Let's do it again.

175
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,960
Five, six, seven, eight.

176
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:01,920
Sister, do you know?

177
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:04,280
The new magistrate was transferred from Chang'an.

178
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,040
They say he is extremely eccentric

179
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,500
and hard to get along with.

180
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,040
I'm starting to envy my dad.

181
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:11,360
He doesn't have to deal with such a difficult superior.

182
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,640
Just be content.

183
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:15,440
As long as the new official loves the people and is just,

184
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,760
he is a good official.

185
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:17,840
True.

186
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,440
Jueming.

187
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,200
Jueming!

188
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:30,770
You haven't said a word since you came back from Yichun Brothel.

189
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:35,280
No, you didn't say anything when you were there either.

190
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:37,560
Is something on your mind?

191
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:40,160
No.

192
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,480
Or did you figure something out?

193
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,440
Smells good.

194
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,120
Let's go in.

195
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:49,520
Let's go.

196
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:57,480
Sit down. I went back and sorted out the whole case.

197
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,440
This Pan Lang...

198
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,920
He robbed Xia Zhiming's tomb.

199
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:03,360
And then, right after that, he borrowed money from the proprietress.

200
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,960
Finally, he died by the moat.

201
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:08,410
Logically speaking, the proprietress is indeed a suspect.

202
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,000
Why are you looking at me?

203
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,200
I'm just analyzing all the possibilities of the case.

204
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,680
Just as the proprietress said.

205
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,440
We were all at Yichun Brothel that day.

206
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,440
She never left her room on the third floor,

207
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,760
so she didn't have time to commit the crime.

208
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,400
We can testify for her.

209
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:30,920
The boss lady usually gives food to homeless children.

210
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,280
She also adopted Jueming.

211
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,920
I really think she is a very, very kind person.

212
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,440
Besides, doesn't murder require a motive?

213
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,280
Yeah.

214
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,760
Losing a dog

215
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:45,140
wouldn't be a reason to kill her husband.

216
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,600
But I think

217
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:50,400
an alcoholic and abusive husband

218
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,560
is worse than a dog.

219
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,720
Right?

220
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,840
In my opinion,

221
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:56,360
we should hurry up and find the Gambling King,

222
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,520
then find out where the fool is,

223
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,880
and look for more clues about Mr. Pan.

224
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,720
Okay, let's go find the Gambling King after we eat.

225
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,920
Yeah.

226
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,800
You go find the Gambling King first.

227
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,600
I'll go to the county office to check the old files.

228
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,520
Let's split up then,

229
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,720
and meet up at the county office later.

230
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,560
Okay.

231
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:40,200
Who is it?

232
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,840
Hello. Who are you?

233
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,120
Well, ma'am,

234
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,690
I want to ask you something.

235
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,760
What do you want to ask?

236
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,000
This household,

237
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:59,080
Xia Zhiming and Xia Chunyi used to live here.

238
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,760
I want to ask, how was their relationship?

239
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,680
Well...

240
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,960
I'm their distant cousin.

241
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,860
I just want to ask about what happened back then.

242
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,560
I heard Xia Zhiming was up to his ears in gambling debt,

243
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,600
so he hid out in this old house.

244
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:23,600
He gambled, drank, and had every vice imaginable.

245
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,300
He treated his wife terribly,

246
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,800
constantly beating and humiliating her.

247
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,880
He usually didn't let Xia Chunyi go out,

248
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:33,760
so I don't know much about his wife.

249
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:37,600
Did the couple keep a dog?

250
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,240
Yes, they did.

251
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:42,320
Xia Zhiming used to complain about having to buy goat's milk for it every day.

252
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:45,380
He said he'd rather use the money to win back his losses.

253
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:48,200
Do you know how he died?

254
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,340
He drank too much and died of illness.

255
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,040
Officers.

256
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:11,760
Xia Zhiming drank excessively for years,

257
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,960
causing disrupted blood flow,

258
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,290
a sudden brain disease,

259
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,280
and his sudden death.

260
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,200
Do you know

261
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,600
who examined Xia Zhiming's body back then?

262
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,280
Zhao Yi'an.

263
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,000
I heard he died too.

264
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,560
But he has a cousin who is also a doctor.

265
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,160
He opened a pharmacy

266
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,880
called Baicao Pharmacy.

267
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,440
Got it.

268
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,880
I was never here today.

269
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:53,680
Why are you here?

270
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:57,560
Actually, when you came over,

271
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,760
I was following you the whole time.

272
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,400
You didn't notice me.

273
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:05,240
I was wondering if something's on your mind.

274
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:06,920
Not at all.

275
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,200
I've just never been to Chunyi's house before,

276
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,530
so I came to look around.

277
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,280
Let's go investigate the case.

278
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:16,650
Do you also suspect the landlady is the murderer?

279
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:23,200
I know the lady boss is your last remaining family.

280
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:26,079
You don't want her to make another mistake.

281
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:29,800
Actually, I was also wondering,

282
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:33,600
if the prime suspect in a case was my father,

283
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:35,080
what I would do.

284
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,600
I think I would do exactly what you did.

285
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,080
I wouldn't tell anyone,

286
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:42,560
investigate the case quietly by myself,

287
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,400
and silently pray for him,

288
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:47,240
hoping things wouldn't get worse.

289
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,080
I want to ask you.

290
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:57,640
If the landlady is really the killer,

291
00:17:58,280 --> 00:17:59,920
would you cover for her?

292
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,000
I want to verify my hypothesis.

293
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,920
It's okay.

294
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,280
It really doesn't matter if you haven't decided.

295
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,440
You still have me,

296
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,080
and us.

297
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,760
We can search for the truth together.

298
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,440
Have you forgotten that our squad

299
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:21,480
shoulders everything together?

300
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,720
Where is Su Lang?

301
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:34,520
Did you agree?

302
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:39,560
Su Lang is with the King of Gamblers.

303
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,240
Alright, let's go check out Baicao Hall.

304
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:46,800
Let's go.

305
00:18:57,280 --> 00:18:59,880
Zhao Yi'an was my cousin.

306
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,280
He passed away from a stroke years ago.

307
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:05,120
When he was alive, he also ran a pharmacy.

308
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:07,600
There weren't many coroners in his area.

309
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,720
So he also did some coroner work on the side.

310
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,000
After he passed away,

311
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,560
I brought over all the patient records

312
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,920
that he had collected.

313
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,480
So some patients who needed to see a doctor for medicine

314
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,280
could still come to me.

315
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,520
Father, I'm heading out.

316
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,000
I want to have soup tonight.

317
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:25,880
Okay.

318
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,400
The mountain roads are slippery.

319
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,920
Remember to be careful.

320
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:32,940
I know, Father.

321
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,520
I'm leaving.

322
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:42,160
That my daughter and I could reconcile,

323
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,440
I really must thank you two.

324
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,000
I wonder if there is anything else

325
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,920
I can help you with this time.

326
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,040
That Pan guy,

327
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:57,960
left you here as collateral before leaving.

328
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,760
A whole day has passed,

329
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:02,560
and he has no intention of paying to redeem you.

330
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,000
Don't blame me.

331
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:06,520
I can only follow the rules

332
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,040
and chop off both your arms first.

333
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,400
Don't be afraid.

334
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:16,480
My blade is very sharp.

335
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,360
My blade is faster.

336
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,320
Keep moving and behave yourself.

337
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:29,960
Hurry up.

338
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,640
Don't try to run. Go.

339
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,120
Tanghulu.

340
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,640
Tanghulu.

341
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,080
So Pan Lang lives here?

342
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,920
This house is abandoned.

343
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,760
My master brought me to stay here temporarily.

344
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:01,090
How long have you lived here with Pan Lang?

345
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:07,160
Good boy.

346
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,240
You are not stupid at all.

347
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:10,760
You lured me into a trap.

348
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,560
Put me down.

349
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,880
My master said

350
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,800
people who wear these clothes are bad.

351
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:18,040
Your master got it backwards. I catch bad guys.

352
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,840
Put me down. Hurry.

353
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,880
Pan Lang is dead.

354
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,480
Liar is a puppy.

355
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:27,200
Do you think this can trap me?

356
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,280
Don't let me catch you.

357
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,320
Tanghulu, one coin a stick.

358
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:33,240
Candied hawthorns! Come and take a look!

359
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:34,200
Little kid,

360
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,640
want a candied hawthorn?

361
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:38,240
Look, they are very sweet.

362
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,400
Pan is my master.

363
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:41,600
Do you have money?

364
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,040
Pan is my master.

365
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,200
No money?

366
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,360
You can't afford candied hawthorns without money.

367
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,690
Get lost, dirty beggar!

368
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,040
Get lost.

369
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,240
Candied hawthorns!

370
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,600
One coin per skewer!

371
00:21:52,640 --> 00:21:54,370
Delicious candied hawthorns!

372
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:59,600
Jueming, you haven't been here for a long time.

373
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,760
I prepared a lot of delicious food for you.

374
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:04,160
Osmanthus cake, peony pastry.

375
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,680
The boss is upstairs.

376
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,280
Should I call her for you?

377
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,600
Mingzhu, no need.

378
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,080
I'll go find her myself.

379
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,650
You go back to your work.

380
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:15,960
What do you want to ask her?

381
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,880
I want you to carefully

382
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,880
watch the candlelight dance one more time.

383
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:18,960
Okay.

384
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:26,720
How is it, Jueming?

385
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,640
The dance is over.

386
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,240
Let's go find Su Lang.

387
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:47,040
Have you figured out the landlady's method?

388
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,560
When we went to her room this morning,

389
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:54,520
I smelled the ash of burnt cardboard.

390
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:01,600
I can tell you three need something from me.

391
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,440
Don't just stand there. Come in.

392
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:22,240
Then what did she burn?

393
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:28,440
Evidence that could prove her method.

394
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:32,800
Look at this.

395
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:34,570
How impressive.

396
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,400
The light and shadow principle of shadow play.

397
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:41,200
It's exactly the same as Sister Chunyi's modus operandi.

398
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:43,480
Yesterday, as we were about to leave,

399
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,320
Sister Chunyi deliberately kept us back to watch the candlelight dance.

400
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,280
During the performance of the candlelight dance,

401
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:51,680
we saw Sister Chunyi's silhouette behind the screen on the second floor.

402
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:53,640
In reality, it was just a piece of cardboard,

403
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,170
not Sister Chunyi herself.

404
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:58,680
The candlelight dance alternates between light and dark.

405
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:02,000
The proprietress knew exactly when it would be light and dark,

406
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,530
so she silently counted the beats in her head,

407
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:08,440
and went downstairs to the moat quickly in the dark.

408
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:14,280
Have you already tried it just now?

409
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:18,320
From the first time the lights went out until the end of the dance,

410
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:21,000
the timing is just right.

411
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:25,920
Well, you two actually have the mood to watch a play.

412
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:28,000
I caught you slacking off.

413
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,360
I've made a major discovery here.

414
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,760
I found Panlang's house.

415
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,280
Take me there.

416
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,040
This way.

417
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:39,480
Okay, okay.

418
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,120
This is where Panlang lives.

419
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:50,320
This kid isn't stupid at all.

420
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:52,120
After making me fall into the trap,

421
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,360
he slipped away.

422
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,760
These are all grave-robbing tools.

423
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:58,890
This is undoubtedly Panlang's house.

424
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:14,080
What exactly is the relationship between this fool and Panlang?

425
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,520
I asked around.

426
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:18,240
Panlang indeed picked up this fool in the ghost market,

427
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,400
and raised him for many years.

428
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,800
At first, he couldn't even speak.

429
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,130
Later, Panlang trained him to be a helper.

430
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,480
It is indeed as Little Mouse said.

431
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:28,240
Although he is foolish, he is honest and obedient.

432
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:30,280
So, when Panlang is robbing graves,

433
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,120
they cooperate with each other.

434
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:40,200
There are bones.

435
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:41,640
Come here.

436
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:45,120
Why didn't I notice it just now?

437
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:47,600
You are amazing, Miss.

438
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,680
These must be Xia Zhiming's bones.

439
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:56,400
Judging from the bone color and shoulder width,

440
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:59,520
the time of death and bone age match Xia Zhiming.

441
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:01,840
But why is there no skull?

442
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:06,280
Look, the gaps between the vertebrae

443
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:08,320
seem to be caused by external force.

444
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:11,760
It seems someone chopped it off with a shovel

445
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,720
and took the skull away.

446
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:18,000
Could there be a secret on the skull?

447
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:20,480
Come look.

448
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:42,200
How is it?

449
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:59,600
Jinglan, head back to the yamen first.

450
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,680
Carefully examine Panlang's head

451
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,720
to check for any external injuries.

452
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:07,680
Brother Su and I will go to Baicao Hall first to find Dr. Wang

453
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,800
and reopen his cousin's coffin for a re-examination.

454
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,080
Okay.

455
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,320
Brothers, dig faster

456
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,640
so we can go back early.

457
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:18,040
Envoy Jueming.

458
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:20,120
My cousin has been buried for so many years.

459
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:22,000
Why the sudden need to open his coffin for an autopsy?

460
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:24,460
There are still many doubts about this case.

461
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:28,400
Could there be another reason for my cousin's death?

462
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,360
It is still unclear.

463
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:32,160
We need to open the coffin for another autopsy.

464
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:34,080
However, without the cover of human skin,

465
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:36,840
the bones will reveal the truth.

466
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,000
If my cousin died an unnatural death,

467
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,400
please, Envoy Jueming, find the truth for him,

468
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:45,040
so he won't die in vain.

469
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,640
Of course.

470
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:17,760
Slow down.

471
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,080
Put it here first. Come.

472
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,200
Come help me hold this.

473
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:06,340
There is a silver needle on the side of the skull.

474
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:28,920
The silver needle entered through the left ear,

475
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,880
passed through the skull,

476
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:36,080
and protruded from the right side by about an inch.

477
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:38,160
This is the real cause of death.

478
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,960
This needle pierced the skull,

479
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,400
causing damage to key meridians.

480
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,530
Pan Lang lost control and fell into the water.

481
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:50,120
After his head hit the stones under the river,

482
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,280
he died.

483
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:54,100
Come, take the evidence back.

484
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,680
You guys bury the coffin.

485
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:07,520
Pan Lang robbed the tomb and dug up Xia Zhiming's remains.

486
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:10,560
He found a silver needle stuck in the skull,

487
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:13,460
and inferred the real cause of Xia Zhiming's death,

488
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:16,560
using this to blackmail Sister Chunyi for money.

489
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:18,120
Madam.

490
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,890
Let's go upstairs and talk.

491
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:25,580
Didn't I give you money this morning?

492
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,760
I was unlucky today and lost it all.

493
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,560
You are really greedy.

494
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,040
I'm telling you,

495
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,840
I won't give you any more money.

496
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,280
Then I'll go,

497
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,920
to report to the authorities,

498
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:56,200
and say there is a silver needle in your husband's skull.

499
00:31:56,560 --> 00:32:01,120
His cause of death needs to be investigated again.

500
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:11,000
I'm off to report it to the authorities.

501
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:13,600
At 7 p.m.,

502
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:16,960
wait for me by the moat.

503
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,800
Bring the head.

504
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:22,960
Money for the evidence.

505
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,240
The pear is too sour.

506
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,240
Peaches are better.

507
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:44,120
Where is the stuff?

508
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,200
Where is the money?

509
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:38,560
What are you doing?

510
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,040
Acai is missing.

511
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,920
Why did you treat it like this?

512
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,400
Are you out of your mind?

513
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:47,680
I'm done! I'm reporting to the authorities right now.

514
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,360
Why would you report this to the authorities?

515
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,690
If you like them so much,

516
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:52,880
let's have one.

517
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:55,140
Then you won't be sad. Let go of me.

518
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:55,960
Let's have one.

519
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:56,840
Let go.

520
00:33:58,600 --> 00:33:59,840
Stop right there.

521
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:03,080
Let go.

522
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:04,360
Let's have another one.

523
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:05,320
Let go.

524
00:34:05,360 --> 00:34:08,040
Help! Let go of me.

525
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:09,679
Help!

526
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,440
When Xia Zhiming died,

527
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,340
my cousin performed the autopsy.

528
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:41,480
Because the silver needle was too deep in the skull,

529
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,480
he didn't find any abnormalities.

530
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,639
Xia Chunyi was afraid of complications,

531
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:49,679
so she silenced him too.

532
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:55,000
He actually found a problem during the autopsy.

533
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:08,920
Officers,

534
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:12,920
Xia Zhiming died suddenly from a brain disease.

535
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:22,480
But greed is human nature.

536
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,680
After Zhao Yi'an learned the secret,

537
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:26,540
he actually tried to control her.

538
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,320
He blackmailed her repeatedly,

539
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,850
and showed up to humiliate her time and again.

540
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:01,240
A worthless thing.

541
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,610
If it's lost, it's lost.

542
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:03,840
If you want,

543
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,280
we can have another one.

544
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:07,720
If you want to keep the secret,

545
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:09,800
you have to stay with me always.

546
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:12,610
Do you still want to live together? Are you crazy?

547
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:32,460
Chunyi made one wrong step, leading to another.

548
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:36,040
She sank deeper into the swamp of mistakes,

549
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:38,740
and eventually murdered Zhao Yi'an.

550
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:42,560
Once your hands are stained with blood,

551
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,760
it's hard to wash them clean.

552
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:48,680
She completely stepped onto a path of no return.

553
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:51,840
To end this haunting nightmare,

554
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,840
Chunyi came to the city

555
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:56,880
and became the proprietress she is today.

556
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:03,720
What I just said is only my guess.

557
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,800
To find the real killer,

558
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,720
we have to visit Baicao Hall again.

559
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:11,440
I think Chunyi and Zhao Yi'an knew each other long ago.

560
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:14,000
After all, giving a false autopsy statement for a stranger

561
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,720
involves huge risks.

562
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:18,120
Dr. Wang.

563
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,400
Please,

564
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:22,320
find all the patient records your cousin collected

565
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:23,600
back then.

566
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:24,480
Okay.

567
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:27,600
Ma'am.

568
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:29,240
Look for girls downstairs.

569
00:37:29,240 --> 00:37:30,700
I don't take clients here.

570
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:34,560
You really are forgetful, Ma'am.

571
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:37,640
I saw you kill Pan Lang.

572
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:32,160
I'm not blind.

